HEADWORD: Speedy
<hw>Speed"y</hw> <pr>(-⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos> <adjf>Speedier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>;
<pos>superl.</pos> <adjf>Speediest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[AS.
<ets>sp⟦emac⟧dyg</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not dilatory or slow; quick; swift;
nimble; hasty; rapid in motion or performance; <as>as, a <ex>speedy</ex>
flight; on <ex>speedy</ex> foot.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I will wish her <qex>speedy</qex> strength.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Darts, which not the good could shun,⟦br⟧
The <qex>speedy</qex> ould outfly.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Speer</ent>⟦br⟧
